<body>

  <!-- @import "site-menubar.kit" -->

  <header class="codebase-docs__header">
    <span><a href="utilities.html">Utilities</a>:</span>
    <h1>Dropdowns</h1>
  </header>

  <!-- @import "site-sidebar.kit" -->

  <p>Dropdowns can be added to buttons or menubar items (for creating child menus).</p>

  <p>
    Examples:
  </p>

  <div class="dropdown">
    <button class="btn btn--primary dropdown__toggle">
      Button with dropdown utility 1
    </button>
    <span class="dropdown__content">
      Example dropdown utility content (that wraps by default)
    </span>
  </div>

  <div class="dropdown">
    <button class="btn btn--primary dropdown__toggle">
      Button with dropdown utility 2
    </button>
    <span class="dropdown__content dropdown__content--nowrap">
      Example dropdown utility content (that doesn't wrap)
    </span>
  </div>
  
  <p>Besides clicking the button again to dismiss the dropdown, you can click anywhere outside the dropdown to dismiss it (i.e. click on a transparent full-screen overlay, which is set at a z-index one unit less than the dropdown).</p>

  <pre><code>&lt;div class="dropdown"&gt;
  &lt;button class="button dropdown__toggle"&gt;
    Button with dropdown utility
  &lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;span class="dropdown__content dropdown__content--nowrap"&gt;
    Example dropdown utility content (that doesn't wrap)
  &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  

  <!-- @import "site-footer.kit" -->

</body>

</html>
